subSection.paragraph:
The organic extract of 

A. argyroxiphii

was purified as reported in detail in the Experimental section to afford six already known phytotoxins, which were identified as porritoxinol (
4
), its closely related phthalide 
5
, its derivative 
6
, zinniol (
7
), alternariol (
8
), and its 4-methyl ether (
9
) (Fig. 1), together with three new compounds: a trisubstituted dihydroisobenzofuranone (
1
), a tetrasubstituted 2-hydroxyethylbenzamide (
2
) and a tetrasubstituted phenyl dihydroxybutyl ether (
3
), named argyrotoxins A-C (
1–3
, Fig. 1).

